@SP
@Kotes

That is so true. Constructors aren’t trying to humiliate you or show how much smarter they are than you, they WANT you to do well. And you’d be surprised at how many answers suddenly make sense just from putting the puzzle down for a while and picking it up later, like your subconscious is grinding away at it while you’re going on about your business.  

I think Wednesdays are a big hill for new solvers to climb, a different animal from Mondays and Tuesdays.  What seems hard now won’t be in a few weeks. You’ll get to know ENO, ONO, OREO, ANA, ANI, EPEE, and many more. The payoff is well worth the effort.

