@SP

While the traditional TRIPLE THREAT for performers is acting, dancing and singing, many of the awardees won for directing, writing, composing, etc.  John Legend, for example, won all four awards, and is known as a singer, composer and producer.  Mel Brooks won as a screenwriter, actor and songwriter (who can forget "Springtime for Hιtler"?).  So that can be a different "triple threat" than the traditional one.  

I'm still not sure the clue is the best possible one, but the clue logically does lead to the answer, and not altogether inaccurate.  I think it's good enough for crosswords, but I can see how less experienced solvers might have a hard time with it.

